            },
            "advisory": "Affected versions of the streamlit package are vulnerable to server-side request forgery (SSRF) due to unsafe path handling that permits UNC/absolute/traversal path inputs to reach filesystem resolution. In lib/streamlit/web/server/component_file_utils.py (and related component/static file handling), path validation occurred too late (after path resolution like os.path.realpath()), which on Windows can interpret attacker-controlled UNC paths and trigger unintended network access; this is fixed by adding centralized checks (e.g., path_security.py / is_unsafe_path_pattern() plus early HTTP-layer blocking) in fix commit 934d2f1 (PR #13733).\r\nhttps://github.com/streamlit/streamlit/commit/934d2f1",
